/// Forward-looking roadmap of pkspec scenarios.
///
/// Every entry here is `reviewStatus = "draft"`, so `pkspec spec --check`
/// ignores them тАФ they exist as a structured TODO list, NOT as a binding
/// commitment. Promote to `specs/Spec.pkl` (and flip `reviewStatus` to
/// `"approved"`) when starting the slice.
///
/// Two listings live in this module:
///   - `entries`         тАФ active draft slices. Spec.pkl flattens this
///                         with `...roadmap.entries`, so anything here
///                         shows up in the rendered SPEC.md as an open
///                         TODO row.
///   - `deferredEntries` тАФ slices we've consciously parked. They keep
///                         their full structure (description, tags,
///                         dependencies) so we can lift them back into
///                         `entries` without re-deriving the scope, but
///                         Spec.pkl does NOT import this listing so it
///                         stays out of the active surface and out of
///                         the rendered SPEC.md.
///
/// 2026-05-16 scope refocus: pkl-mbt is being positioned as a MoonBit
/// library (parser / typechecker / evaluator surface). Slices that
/// overlap Apple Pkl's own runtime tooling moved into the deferred
/// listing тАФ reviving any of them is a one-line move back into
/// `entries`:
///   - PKL-101 (repl)               тАФ interactive CLI, low library value
///   - PKL-126b (xml renderer)      тАФ covered by `pkl eval -f xml` upstream
///   - PKL-126c (protobuf renderer) тАФ same; needs `.proto` schema parser
///   - PKL-127 (renderer converters) тАФ same renderer surface
///   - PKL-129b2 (package unpack)   тАФ `pkl download-package` + `--module-path`
///                                    covers it; ZIP/DEFLATE/SHA-256/cache is
///                                    a multi-KLOC slice for thin marginal
///                                    library value over PKL-129b1's diagnostic
///   - PKL-130 (pkldoc)             тАФ pkl's own `pkldoc` covers this
///   - PKL-132 (LSP)                тАФ out of scope for the library slice
///
/// Active entries focus on upstream Apple Pkl compatibility тАФ the
/// 2026-05-17 probe across 488 candidate fixtures surfaced concrete
/// gaps the slices below address in projected uplift order
/// (`PKL-148` first now that PKL-147 has landed). The deferred listing
/// tracks the slices we consciously parked; revive one of them into
/// `entries` when a concrete library consumer asks for the shape.
///
/// Recently landed:
///   PKL-119a/b/c/d/be Pair / IntSeq / Set / Map / IntSeq-eq value-variant work
///   PKL-129b1         package:// URI parse + metadata fetch + diagnostic
///   PKL-131 / 131b    codegen bridge тАФ MoonBit target (struct / typealias)
///   PKL-143           pkl:reflect class / module introspection
///   PKL-144 / 145     pkl:json.Parser.parse + hidden class-property modifier
///   PKL-146           pkl:yaml.Parser.parse via moonbit-community/yaml
///   PKL-147           snippetTest harness foundation (parser amend body
///                     dispatch, module.catch, hex/bin/oct ints,
///                     output.text / omitNullProperties; +3 gold-match
///                     fixtures, 33 тЖТ 35)
///   PKL-148 (1st)     pkl:base method surface first wave (Bool / Float /
///                     Int / String / Listing / Mapping / Set / Map / Pair
///                     additions, getClass mirror, class-default expansion
///                     for typed empty new {}, Apple Pkl-aligned constraint
///                     diagnostic wording, +/concat for collection variants;
///                     +3 gold-match fixtures, 35 тЖТ 38)
///   PKL-148b (2nd)    `this <op> N` constraint, `as` / `|>` operators,
///                     Duration / DataSize scalar arithmetic, Set+Listing,
///                     Int.isBetween / .toFloat, Listing.isDistinctBy,
///                     Listing-host constraint (`Listing<T>(!isEmpty)`),
///                     construction-time constraint enforcement;
///                     +2 gold-match fixtures, 38 тЖТ 40
///   PKL-148c (3rd)    runtime evaluation of arbitrary constraint
///                     expressions (`Int(abs < 100)`, `Address(street.
///                     endsWith("St."))`, `Int(this >= min)`) via parser
///                     reuse + implicit-receiver AST rewrite, +
///                     Apple Pkl-aligned `if` condition diagnostic;
///                     +3 gold-match fixtures, 40 тЖТ 43
///   PKL-148d (4th)    class-as-value reflect mirror, lexical scope
///                     walk (env > module bindings, local property hoist
///                     with @hidden$ prefix strip), deep-merge amend
///                     semantics for nested ObjectValues, class-name
///                     hint in constraint diagnostics; +7 gold-match
///                     fixtures, 43 тЖТ 50
///   PKL-148e (5th)    object-body forward refs, amend-body super (simple
///                     form), Function.apply / applyToList / toString /
///                     getClass, stdlib class-as-value mirror (Int / Float
///                     / List / Set / Map / Pair / IntSeq / Function /
///                     ...), bodyless `class Foo` parser fix, `local`
///                     class property + sibling class methods visible
///                     to method bodies, `local name { body }` (untyped
///                     local amend), leading-dot Float literal, heredoc
///                     trailing-newline strip, Any / List / Collection /
///                     Set / user-class loose runtime acceptance;
///                     +10 gold-match fixtures, 50 тЖТ 60
///   PKL-148f (6th)    multiset Set equality, unordered Object / Map /
///                     Mapping equality, IntSeq equality via Int64
///                     length (no materialise), no-arg property forms
///                     callable as `.method()` on String / Int / Float
///                     / Listing, Float property surface
///                     (eval_float_property), module-level `hidden h =`
///                     bare-name lookup, typed-property default
///                     synthesis for user classes / nullable / string
///                     literal / *union / Listing / Mapping / Set / Map,
///                     `extends` parent class scope inherited through
///                     analysis-side import resolver; +7 gold-match
///                     fixtures, 60 тЖТ 67
///   PKL-148g (7th)    FunctionValue identity stamp (lambda equality is
///                     reference-based, not structural), virtual class
///                     method dispatch (parent тЖТ derived push order),
///                     `local <modifier>* name` parsing, `this.X` in
///                     object body short-circuits to sibling resolver
///                     when X is a binding; +5 gold-match fixtures,
///                     67 тЖТ 72
///   PKL-148h (8th)    ListValue split from ListingValue тАФ `List(...)`
///                     and `.toList()` produce a dedicated variant that
///                     renders through Apple Pkl's `List(elem, ...)`
///                     constructor form (`ListingValue` keeps the
///                     `new { ... }` block form); listing-method
///                     dispatch / `+` / subscript / type-acceptance /
///                     constraint walker accept both variants via
///                     pattern alternation; subscript out-of-bounds
///                     diagnostic switched to Apple Pkl's wording so
///                     `module.catch(...)` strings round-trip; +10
///                     gold-match fixtures, 72 тЖТ 82. Subsumes the
///                     drafted PKL-151 listVariantSplit.
///   PKL-148i (9th)    Literal-valued class property assignments now
///                     reject when the value's runtime type does not
///                     satisfy the declared annotation
///                     (`new Person { name = 42 }` тЖТ
///                     "Expected value of type `String`, but got
///                     type `Int`. Value: 42"). Parent-class
///                     annotations are inherited when a subclass
///                     redeclares the property without its own
///                     annotation (Person3 inherits Person.name).
///                     Free-form expression bodies stay deferred тАФ
///                     the surrounding forward-binding leak from a
///                     sibling object literal can silently re-bind
///                     an identifier to the wrong scalar, so a
///                     blanket rejection masks unrelated fixtures'
///                     gold output. +14 gold-match fixtures
///                     (1 caused by the new check, 13 free
///                     promotions surfaced by the same probe pass:
///                     listings2/listing1, mappings2/mapping1, the
///                     projects/ cluster, errors/baseModule,
///                     parser/trailingCommas+constraintsTrailingComma,
///                     types/helpers/someModule), 82 тЖТ 96.
///   PKL-148j (10th)   Split the `@hidden$` storage prefix into a
///                     dedicated `@local$` form so external member
///                     access (`(target).x`) hides `local`
///                     declarations while still resolving
///                     `hidden`-modifier properties (Apple Pkl's
///                     distinction). Missing `Collection<T>` /
///                     `List<T>` auto-default also routes to
///                     `ListValue([])`. Follow-up: amend merge now
///                     uses strict storage-name matching so the
///                     local namespace (`@local$l`) and the visible
///                     namespace (bare `l`) stay independent slots
///                     across an amend body. +4 gold-match fixtures:
///                     `basic/localProperty2`,
///                     `basic/propertyDefaults`,
///                     `basic/localPropertyOverride1`,
///                     `basic/localPropertyOverride2`, 96 тЖТ 100.
///   PKL-148k (11th)   Mapping literal duplicate-key detection.
///                     Apple Pkl rejects two entries that resolve
///                     to the same scalar key inside a single
///                     `new Mapping { ... }` body with `Duplicate
///                     definition of member \`"X"\`.`. The check is
///                     gated on scalar key shapes (String / Int /
///                     Float / Bool / Null / Duration / DataSize /
///                     Regex / Bytes) тАФ composite keys (ObjectValue
///                     / ListingValue / MappingValue) would
///                     false-positive against `mappings/mapping1`'s
///                     `new Dynamic {}` / `new Person {}` keys
///                     without class-aware equality, deferred to
///                     PKL-148m. Pipe-operator (`|>`) projects the
///                     Apple-Pkl-shaped diagnostic for non-callable
///                     RHS (`module.catch(() -> 42 |> 21)` тЖТ
///                     `Operator \`|>\` is not defined for operand
///                     types \`Int\` and \`Int\`. Left operand : 42
///                     Right operand: 21`) instead of the generic
///                     `call expects Function`. +2 gold-match
///                     fixtures, 100 тЖТ 102.
///   PKL-148l (12th)   Callable-parameter basic-type rejection
///                     fires before the body runs (`x.sum(1.1, 2)`
///                     against `sum(a: Int, b: Int): Int` now
///                     projects `Expected value of type \`Int\`,
///                     but got type \`Float\`. Value: 1.1` instead
///                     of running the body and bubbling an
///                     `operator + expects Int operands` from
///                     deep inside). Mirrors the return-side
///                     acceptance pipeline (type alias resolution
///                     тЖТ strip `(...)` constraint тЖТ strip `<...>`
///                     generic head тЖТ run `eval_value_accepts_type_annotation`
///                     + `value_satisfies_user_class_annotation`)
///                     at all three callable entry points
///                     (`eval_lambda_application`,
///                     `apply_function_value`, class-method
///                     dispatch). Generic-head stripping prevents
///                     false-positive on `List<Set<...>>`-shaped
///                     annotations in `types/ThisInTypeConstraint`.
///                     +1 gold-match fixture, 102 тЖТ 103.
///   PKL-148m (13th)   `local` modifier on `class`, `function`,
///                     `typealias` declarations was silently dropped
///                     by the parser (the whole member routed
///                     through `skip_unknown_member`), so
///                     `local class C { ... }` /
///                     `local function f(...): ... = ...` /
///                     `local typealias T = Int(...)` never reached
///                     the declaration list тАФ references later in
///                     the module raised `Cannot find property`,
///                     stamped-empty ObjectValue for `new C {}`, or
///                     silently bypassed a typealias's runtime
///                     constraint. Now consumes the `local` token
///                     and dispatches to the appropriate parser
///                     (record the declaration unchanged; the
///                     cross-module export-suppression side is a
///                     separate concern that doesn't gate any
///                     current gold fixture). +6 fixtures, 103 тЖТ
///                     109 (`basic/localMethodTyped3`,
///                     `basic/localModuleMemberOverride1`,
///                     `modules/amendModule5`,
///                     `types/typeAliasConstraint1`,
///                     `implementation/equality`,
///                     `implementation/inequality`).
///   PKL-148n (14th)   Infrastructure split for the asAndPipeRuntime
///                     (PKL-150) cluster: (1) `as` strips both the
///                     trailing `(...)` constraint and any `<...>`
///                     generic head before the acceptance check, so
///                     `Set(...) as Set<Listing<Int>>` accepts the
///                     outer SetValue without iterating elements
///                     (matches Apple Pkl's shape-preserving runtime
///                     `as`); (2) `local NAME = EXPR` declarations
///                     interleaved with element expressions inside
///                     a Listing body are no longer dropped by
///                     `parse_listing_body` тАФ the parser captures
///                     each body item as Element or LocalBinding
///                     and desugars the chain into nested `let`
///                     wrapped in `WhenSpread`, reusing existing
///                     evaluator machinery instead of adding a new
///                     Expr variant; `parse_inferred_new_body` also
///                     gained a `skip_local_decls_from` look-ahead
///                     so `{ local тАж ; bare-expr }` routes to the
///                     listing parser. No gold-match flip on this
///                     slice alone (the `basic/as*` fixtures still
///                     need `pkl:test.catch` / `catchOrNull` and
///                     per-element constraint deferral work). The
///                     PKL-152 (`anyTypeCoercion`) roadmap entry is
///                     also retired тАФ `Any` already accepts every
///                     runtime value via the `("Any", _) => true`
///                     arm in `eval_value_accepts_type_annotation`
///                     (landed with PKL-148e).
///   PKL-148o (15th)   `catch` / `catchOrNull` wiring plus bare
///                     constraint diagnostic wording. Three Apple-
///                     Pkl alignment fixes: (1) `module.catchOrNull`
///                     / `test.catchOrNull` was unwired тАФ eval
///                     surfaced `Cannot find property catchOrNull`;
///                     a new CallExpr intercept + helper routes
///                     through the shared catch outcome core,
///                     returning `null` on the no-throw branch;
///                     (2) `catch(fun)` on a non-throwing lambda
///                     returned the rendered value as a string тАФ
///                     Apple Pkl's `TestNodes.catchMethod` raises
///                     `Expected an exception, but none was thrown.`
///                     instead; (3) the callable-parameter
///                     constraint check wrapped its bare upstream
///                     message with `<label> argument N` prefix at
///                     all three eval entry points тАФ Apple Pkl
///                     emits the bare form per
///                     `errorMessages.properties#typeConstraintViolated`.
///                     Dropping the prefix at every eval call site
///                     (the typecheck-side wording is unaffected)
///                     plus updating four affected unit tests to
///                     the bare form. No gold-match flip тАФ the
///                     `basic/as*` and `methods/methodParameterConstraints2`
///                     fixtures that exercise these paths still need
///                     the broader per-element constraint deferral
///                     and runtime constraint expression eval for
///                     lambdas with closures, both deferred to the
///                     super-late-bind cluster.
///   PKL-148p (16th)   Shebang preamble (`#!/usr/bin/env pkl eval`)
///                     at module start was unhandled by the lexer
///                     тАФ the leading `#` surfaced as `unsupported
///                     expression`, so `syntax/shebang.pkl` failed
///                     before reaching its `foo = 1` body. The fix
///                     is a tiny lexer-level branch in
///                     `Lexer::next_token`: when `pos == 0` and the
///                     first two bytes are `#!`, consume the line
///                     to the next `\n` and emit a `comment()`
///                     trivia token so the existing trivia-skip
///                     logic absorbs it the same way as `//`. The
///                     `pos == 0` guard keeps a stray `#!` later
///                     in the source from being silently swallowed
///                     (Apple Pkl only special-cases the preamble
///                     shebang). +1 fixture (`syntax/shebang`),
///                     109 тЖТ 110.
///   PKL-148q (17th)   `output.text` was emitted via `println(text)`,
///                     which always appends `\n` and skewed the byte
///                     count for `api/moduleOutput` (gold ends
///                     without `\n`). Routing the text bypass
///                     through `@fs.write_string_to_file(
///                     "/dev/stdout", text)` gets verbatim emit
///                     without a new FFI dep. Simultaneously
///                     hardened the smoke gate: `eval_matches_gold`
///                     used to capture stdout via `$(...)` + re-emit
///                     through `printf '%s\n'`, silently normalising
///                     the final byte; switched to
///                     `mpkl eval > tmpfile; diff -u gold tmpfile`
///                     for true byte-for-byte comparison (which is
///                     the contract the README advertises). +1
///                     fixture (`api/moduleOutput`), 110 тЖТ 111.
///   PKL-148r (18th)   Triple-dot import (`import ".../X/Y.pkl"`)
///                     walks parent directories of the importing
///                     module to find the first ancestor that
///                     contains the remainder path; Apple Pkl's
///                     test corpus uses this 51 times. CLI side
///                     (`@fs.path_exists`) does the FS walk and
///                     caches the resolution into a sandbox-level
///                     `(from, uri) -> resolved` map; the IO-free
///                     analysis layer consults the map so eval-time
///                     cache lookups agree with the path the CLI
///                     loaded under. +3 fixtures (`classes/
///                     constraints14`, `errors/const/
///                     constLocalAmendModule`, `modules/
///                     amendModule6`), 111 тЖТ 114. Remaining
///                     triple-dot fixtures need orthogonal work
///                     (`pkl:shell`, `pkl:yaml` parser flags,
///                     jsonnet renderer, `pkl:reflect.Module.
///                     imports`, `ConvertProperty` annotation
///                     framework, package registry resolution).
///   PKL-148s (19th)   Spread members (`...x` / `...?x`) in object
///                     / listing / mapping bodies. The body parsers
///                     were routing the leading `...` dots to
///                     `skip_unknown_member`, so any fixture using
///                     spread reported `unsupported expression`.
///                     Object body now pushes
///                     `ObjectMember { name = "@spread" }` (slots
///                     into the existing `@when` / `@for` sentinel
///                     dispatch in `eval_object_members`); listing
///                     and mapping bodies wrap the payload in the
///                     pre-existing `WhenSpread(...)` synthetic
///                     entry so the eval-side spread-flatten path
///                     already covers them. `Some(NullValue) => ()`
///                     arms added to the listing / mapping
///                     evaluators so `...?x` against null is a no-
///                     op. +1 fixture (`generators/
///                     spreadSyntaxNullable`), 114 тЖТ 115. The
///                     remaining spread fixtures
///                     (`spreadSyntaxDynamic`, `spreadSyntaxListing`,
///                     `spreadSyntaxTyped`, `spreadSyntaxMapping`)
///                     need the unified Dynamic value variant
///                     (named members + unnamed elements in one
///                     shape), deferred to the super-late-bind
///                     cluster.
///   PKL-148t (20th)   Callable return / argument type checks now
///                     resolve aliases, strip generic heads, and
///                     split top-level unions before the value-side
///                     acceptance check (`Parameterized` тЖТ
///                     `List<String>` тЖТ `List`; `Union` тЖТ
///                     `Int|Boolean` тЖТ check `Int` then `Boolean`).
///                     `resolve_binding_value` also falls through
///                     to a sibling module-level function when a
///                     property's RHS self-references the same
///                     name (`qux = qux(...)` beside `function
///                     qux(...) = ...`), instead of surfacing a
///                     cyclic-property diagnostic. +1 fixture
///                     (`methods/methodParameterConstraints1`),
///                     115 тЖТ 116. The typeAlias* fixtures need
///                     additional per-property lazy class
///                     instantiation (so `test.catch(() ->
///                     bad.res13)` isolates one property's check
///                     rather than re-evaluating all 12 on `new
///                     Bad {}`), deferred.
///   PKL-148u (21st)   Structural type rejection + lazy per-
///                     property class-default semantics. (1) New
///                     `eval_resolved_annotation_structural_rejection_message`
///                     fires on type-shape mismatches independently
///                     of any constraint predicate (`res: String =
///                     42` rejects with the right diagnostic);
///                     aliases resolve, unions split, generics
///                     strip, collections recurse element-wise.
///                     (2) `eval_object_members_with_options(...
///                     defer_property_errors~)` captures each
///                     class-default property's diagnostics into a
///                     per-property buffer and encodes failures as
///                     `@error$<name>` sentinel members on the
///                     resulting ObjectValue; the `MemberAccess`
///                     arm raises that property's diagnostic at
///                     access time via `lookup_pending_error_message`.
///                     `test.catch(() -> bad.res13)` and
///                     `test.catch(() -> bad.res14)` now isolate
///                     each other's outcomes even though `bad`
///                     itself is cached after first construction.
///                     Callable + binding diagnostics also align
///                     with Apple Pkl's wording: quote the resolved
///                     type name (strip trailing `?`), so `Nullable
///                     = Duration?` shows as `Duration`. +2
///                     fixtures (`types/typeAlias1`,
///                     `modules/typedModuleMethods1`), 116 тЖТ 118.
///   PKL-148v (22nd)   Class parent typealias resolution. `class
///                     Baz extends Bar` where `typealias Bar = Foo`
///                     was losing `Foo`'s default-property
///                     inheritance because `eval_class_default_members`
///                     ran the recursive parent lookup directly
///                     through `lookup_class_binding`; `Bar` isn't
///                     a class so the lookup returned None. One-
///                     spot fix: run `parent_name` through
///                     `eval_resolved_type_alias` before recursing.
///                     +1 fixture (`types/typeAlias2`), 118 тЖТ 119;
///                     types category 29.4% тЖТ 35.3%.
///   PKL-148w (23rd)   Subscript-amend on Listing: `(listing) {
///                     [N] = newValue }` replaces element N (with
///                     `Element index \`<n>\` is out of range \`0\`..
///                     \`<upper>\`.` on out-of-bound). Parser
///                     captures each `[key] = value` inside an
///                     object body as a synthetic
///                     `@subscript$<offset>` ObjectMember whose
///                     value is `CallExpr(Identifier("@__index_entry"),
///                     [key, value])` тАФ no AST variant needed.
///                     AmendExpr's ListingValue / ListValue arm
///                     decodes the marker and dispatches through
///                     `eval_listing_subscript_amend`. +1 fixture
///                     (`listings/wrongIndex`), 119 тЖТ 120; listings
///                     category 18.8% тЖТ 25.0%.
///   PKL-148x (24th)   Dynamic value shape via sentinel member
///                     names. Parser captures bare expressions in
///                     an object body as `@element$<offset>`
///                     ObjectMembers and `[key] = value` as
///                     `@subscript$<offset>` (PKL-148w encoding);
///                     eval evaluates each sentinel and keeps the
///                     prefix; renderer projects `@element$`
///                     listing-style (via `render_pcf_inline` so
///                     nested objects pick up the `new ` prefix)
///                     and `@subscript$` as `[key] = value`. The
///                     `@spread` arm now lowers Listing / List /
///                     Set payloads to `@element$spread<i>` and
///                     Mapping / Map payloads to `@subscript$spread<i>`,
///                     so `new { ...listing }` etc. flatten into
///                     the parent Dynamic. `parse_inferred_new_body`
///                     routes `{ ...x }` through the object-body
///                     parser since the Dynamic shape now absorbs
///                     every payload shape. +2 fixtures
///                     (`generators/spreadSyntaxTyped`,
///                     `generators/forGeneratorNestedReference2`),
///                     120 тЖТ 122; generators category 9.5% тЖТ 19.0%.
///   PKL-148y (25th)   Listing-amend body tolerates `when` / `for`
///                     / spread / `@element$` generator members.
///                     `eval_listing_subscript_amend` now splices
///                     each generator's payload (ListingValue /
///                     ListValue / SetValue) onto the running
///                     result in source order before the next
///                     `@subscript$` entry applies. +1 fixture
///                     (`listings2/wrongIndex` тАФ
///                     `when (false) {0}; [3] = "barn owl"`),
///                     122 тЖТ 123; listings2 category 10.0% тЖТ 20.0%.
///   PKL-148aa (26th)  Super property access in class default body.
///                     `eval_class_default_members` pushes
///                     `super = ObjectValue(base_values)` into a
///                     cache copy before evaluating the class's
///                     own defaults so `super.value` inside a
///                     property body resolves against the parent
///                     class's already-evaluated defaults. Method
///                     dispatch via `eval_super_method_call`
///                     (`@current_class` marker) is unchanged.
///                     +1 fixture (`classes/supercallsInLet`),
///                     123 тЖТ 124; classes category 52.9% тЖТ 55.9%.
///   PKL-148ab (27th)  Class methods bare-name resolution in
///                     class default body. The class's own
///                     methods are pushed as `FunctionValue`s
///                     into the same `defaults_cache` so a
///                     property body like `x = f()` resolves
///                     `f` against the class's lexical method
///                     set. Each `FunctionValue` shares the
///                     live `defaults_cache` reference, so
///                     mutually-recursive methods see each
///                     other at call time. Lexical (not
///                     virtual): inherited methods don't
///                     override the declaring class's local
///                     method. +3 fixtures
///                     (`basic/localMethodOverride1`,
///                     `localMethodOverride2`,
///                     `localMethodTyped4`), 124 тЖТ 127;
///                     basic category 39.5% тЖТ 43.0%.
///   PKL-148ac (28th)  Module-level super dispatch for
///                     `extends`. `eval_program` eagerly
///                     loads the parent module and pushes
///                     `super = ObjectValue(parent_members)`
///                     into the cache so module-level
///                     functions / hidden properties capture
///                     it. `eval_super_method_call` falls
///                     back to looking up the method in the
///                     super-bound ObjectValue (under both
///                     bare and hidden_member_name keys) and
///                     applies it via `apply_function_value`
///                     when `@current_class` is absent. +3
///                     fixtures (`modules/supercalls2`,
///                     `amendModule4`, `extendModule1`),
///                     127 тЖТ 130; modules category 61.9% тЖТ
///                     76.2%.
///   PKL-148ad (29th)  At-prefix local dep import resolution.
///                     `resolve_at_prefix_dep` in the CLI
///                     walks `from` upward for
///                     `PklProject.deps.json`, JSON-parses
///                     via `@json.parse`, finds the dep by
///                     short name, and тАФ when local-type тАФ
///                     combines PklProject dir + dep.path +
///                     rest. Registered in the same sandbox
///                     cache the triple-dot loader uses; the
///                     eval-side resolver in analysis.mbt
///                     consults that cache for `@`-prefix
///                     URIs. Remote-type deps still defer to
///                     PKL-129. +1 fixture
///                     (`projects/project7/spacesInImport`),
///                     130 тЖТ 131; projects category 36.8% тЖТ
///                     42.1%.
///   PKL-148ae (30th)  Constraint cascade extends to
///                     `List<X(...)>` / `Map<K(...), V(...)>`
///                     element walks plus `T(...)?` nullable
///                     unwrap. Adds `isEmpty` / `!isEmpty`
///                     String predicates and drops the
///                     `<label> return ` prefix from the
///                     return-side diagnostic to match Apple
///                     Pkl's parameter-side wording (PKL-148o).
///                     +1 fixture
///                     (`methods/methodParameterConstraints2`),
///                     131 тЖТ 132; methods category 60.0% тЖТ
///                     80.0%.
///   PKL-148af (31st)  Callable arg type rejection walks
///                     collection elements after head accept.
///                     `eval_callable_argument_type_rejection_message`
///                     recurses through each element / entry
///                     for `List<X>` / `Listing<X>` /
///                     `Set<X>` / `Map<K, V>` /
///                     `Mapping<K, V>` arguments so
///                     `f3(List("foo", 42))` against
///                     `x: List<String>` surfaces the inner
///                     `Int` mismatch via the same
///                     `"Expected value of type тАж but got
///                     type тАж"` wording. +1 fixture
///                     (`basic/localTypedModuleMember`),
///                     132 тЖТ 133; basic category 43.0% тЖТ
///                     44.2%.
///   PKL-148ag (32nd)  Object-body `local function f(...)`
///                     parses as a lambda member +
///                     unresolvable type annotation surfaces
///                     `Cannot find type` diagnostic.
///                     `parse_object_body_members` reuses
///                     `parse_function_decl` and lowers to
///                     `@local$f = LambdaExpr(...)`;
///                     `eval_type_name_is_unresolvable`
///                     short-circuits both callable parameter
///                     and return rejection paths to the
///                     `Cannot find type \`<name>\`.` wording
///                     when the annotation doesn't name a
///                     known type. +6 fixtures
///                     (`basic/localMethodInAmendingModule`,
///                     `basic/localMethodTyped`,
///                     `basic/localMethodTyped2`,
///                     `basic/localMethodTyped5`,
///                     `basic/localMethodTyped6`,
///                     `basic/localMethodUntyped`),
///                     133 тЖТ 139; basic category 44.2% тЖТ
///                     51.2%.
///   PKL-148ah (33rd)  `module.<self>.<sibling>` reads the
///                     in-progress partial object instead of
///                     cycling, and `module.X` in an `amends`
///                     / `extends` child falls back through
///                     `super` so parent-only names resolve.
///                     `eval_object_members` pushes
///                     `{ name: <stack_top>, value:
///                     ObjectValue(values_snapshot) }` into
///                     per-field `local_env`; the `module.X`
///                     short-circuit chains to
///                     `lookup_value(cache, "super")` тЖТ
///                     `lookup_member` when the primary
///                     binding lookup returns None. +2
///                     fixtures (`basic/moduleRef1`,
///                     `basic/moduleRef2`), 139 тЖТ 141;
///                     basic category 51.2% тЖТ 53.5%.
///   PKL-148ai (34th)  String-literal singleton type
///                     (`"Pigeon"` as a union choice) +
///                     `endsWith` / `startsWith` /
///                     `contains` (plus negations) string
///                     constraint predicates.
///                     `eval_value_accepts_type_annotation`
///                     gains a leading-`"`-and-trailing-`"`
///                     literal arm; `ConstraintStringPredicate`
///                     gains six variants and
///                     `pkl_string_constraint_predicate`
///                     recognises the bare and `this.`-prefixed
///                     forms with quoted-string arguments. +1
///                     fixture (`basic/letTyped`), 141 тЖТ 142;
///                     basic category 53.5% тЖТ 54.7%.
///   PKL-148aj (35th)  Object-body member-header dispatch
///                     absorbs `const` and other modifier
///                     prefixes. Collapsed the two pre-passes
///                     (`consume_member_visibility_modifiers` +
///                     `skip_member_header`) into a single
///                     `consume_member_header` loop that handles
///                     annotations / visibility / modifier idents
///                     in any order, and added a
///                     `skip_member_prefix_from` helper so
///                     `parse_inferred_new_body` routes any
///                     modifier-led body (`const baz`,
///                     `const local function biz`) to
///                     `parse_object_body` instead of silently
///                     dropping into `parse_listing_body`. +1
///                     fixture (`basic/constModifier4`),
///                     142 тЖТ 143; basic category 54.7% тЖТ 55.8%.
///   PKL-148ak (36th)  Deferred `@error$<name>` sentinels stop
///                     leaking into the rendered output and now
///                     fire on bare-identifier reads from
///                     sibling expressions. Moved the
///                     `@error$` prefix into `parser.mbt` so
///                     `is_invisible_member_name` filters it
///                     out of every renderer; extended
///                     `eval_object_members`'s hoisting loop to
///                     also push the sentinel into per-field
///                     `local_env` under `@error$<bare>`; added
///                     an env intercept in the
///                     `eval_expr_with_bindings` Identifier arm
///                     so `test.catch(() -> bad_local)` captures
///                     the type / constraint rejection diagnostic
///                     instead of seeing the type-invalid value.
///                     +1 fixture (`basic/localTypedClassMember`),
///                     143 тЖТ 144; basic category 55.8% тЖТ 57.0%.
@ModuleInfo { minPklVersion = "0.31.0" }
module specs.Roadmap

import "../pkspec/Spec.pkl"

// тФАтФА ACTIVE тФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФА
// Slices below were identified by running every upstream
// `LanguageSnippetTests/input/<subtree>/*.pkl` fixture through the
// CLI on 2026-05-17 and categorizing the first-line diagnostic. The
// probe surfaced 488 candidates, 33 already gold-match, 156 fail
// with a diagnostic, 148 evaluate without error but the rendered
// output diverges from the gold. The slices are ordered by
// projected upstream-uplift (largest first); each one names the
// fixture category it should unblock so progress is measurable
// against `scripts/upstream-smoke.sh` after each landing.

local pklSuperLateBindAndAmendLambda: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-148al"
  name = "super late binding amend lambda form class-aware object equality"
  description =
    "PKL-148ai added the string-literal singleton type arm and `endsWith` / `startsWith` / `contains` string constraint predicates (+1 fixture, 141 тЖТ 142; basic 53.5% тЖТ 54.7%); PKL-148aj collapsed the object-body member-header into one pass and taught `parse_inferred_new_body` to peek through arbitrary modifier prefixes so `const`-led members route to `parse_object_body` instead of being lost in `parse_listing_body` (+1 fixture, 142 тЖТ 143; basic 54.7% тЖТ 55.8%); PKL-148ak folded the `@error$` deferred-rejection prefix into the invisible-member set, hoisted the sentinel into per-field env, and added an Identifier intercept so `test.catch(() -> bad_local)` captures the deferred diagnostic against typed locals (+1 fixture, 143 тЖТ 144; basic 55.8% тЖТ 57.0%). The harder remaining pieces тАФ all of which require non-local evaluator work тАФ are: full Apple-Pkl `super.X` late binding (re-evaluate the parent's RHS against the amended this, needed for `objects/super2` / `super3` / `super4`, `classes/supercallsInLet`, and `basic/moduleRef3`'s `const a = 44` override of the parent's `aa = module.a`); the `(lambda) { body }` amend form for lambdas that return lambdas (used by `lambdas/amendLambda*` fixtures); runtime constraint expression eval that resolves user-defined `function` calls (`multiply(subtract(add(5,4),3),2) == z` from `classes/constraints7`); constraints firing on amend chains where the host class isn't statically known (constraints11 / 12 / 13); class-aware ObjectValue tagging so `new Person {} != new Person2 {}` (needed for `objects/equality`'s c-block + composite Mapping keys in `mappings/mapping1` that PKL-148k currently sidesteps via a scalar-only duplicate-check gate тАФ a prototype hidden `__class` marker landed in PKL-148i but was reverted after it broke 14 structural-equality unit tests; the right shape is a dedicated `ObjectValue(class_name: String?, members)` enum-shape refactor); the `pipeOperator` res11 diagnostic also needs the class-aware tag to project `pipeOperator#Person` / `new Person {}`; object-body amend chain (`(obj) { ... } { ... }` тАФ needed for `objects/equality` a11); free-form (non-literal) amend-override rejections (`(res3) { y = expr }` against `Int(this > x)` constraints тАФ gated today on the upstream forward-binding leak where a sibling object's `local x = 1` resolves into a later object body's identifier lookup); listing/mapping body re-eval on amend so listing `(x) {}` / `default = N` work (needed for `listings/equality`, `listings/inequality`, `mappings/equality`, `mappings/inequality`). Listing/List-method receiver-tag preservation (`list.map(...)` returns a List, `listing.map(...)` returns a Listing) is a sub-task too; today the dispatcher always re-wraps as ListingValue. Remaining stdlib gaps (DataSize.isBinaryUnit, Duration.isBetween, jsonnet renderer module) ride along."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-148ak" }
  tags { "evaluator"; "stdlib"; "upstream"; "compat"; "next" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

local upstreamResourceType: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-149"
  name = "Resource type for read return values"
  description =
    "Apple Pkl's `read(\"file:...\")` returns a `Resource` value carrying `.uri` / `.text` / `.base64` / `.md5` / `.sha256` accessors; pkl-mbt currently returns the file contents as a bare `String`. Introduce a `ResourceValue` variant, route `read(\"file:...\")` through it, and wire the property accessors. Also stop rejecting bare paths (the upstream `api/Resource` fixture passes `read(\"empty.txt\")` without a scheme тАФ Apple Pkl treats it as `file:` relative to the module). Required for the `api/Resource*` / `api/read*` upstream fixture cluster."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-098" }
  tags { "evaluator"; "stdlib"; "upstream"; "compat" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

local asAndPipeRuntime: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-150"
  name = "as and pipe operator runtime semantics"
  description =
    "PKL-148n landed the foundational pieces (`as` strips the trailing constraint and generic head so `Set(...) as Set<Listing<Int>>` accepts the outer SetValue; `|>` already projects Apple Pkl's diagnostic for non-callable RHS via PKL-148k; `local NAME = EXPR` inside Listing bodies now desugars into a `WhenSpread(let(...) body)` chain so the `basic/as*` fixtures' inline locals parse through). The remaining work needed before `basic/as`, `basic/as2`, `basic/as3`, and `lambdas/pipeOperator` byte-match the gold: (1) `pkl:test.catch` / `catchOrNull` currently runs the no-throw branch but returns the wrapped value uncasted тАФ Apple Pkl returns the value as-is and the surrounding `== null` / pcf-render comparison drives the example output (needs the lambda body to evaluate THROUGH the lambda before catch decides whether to surface the result or the diagnostic); (2) per-element constraint deferral тАФ `Set(new Listing { 'one' }) as Set<Listing<Int>>` accepts the outer SetValue at cast time, but reading `s2.first[0]` must fire the inner `Listing<Int>` constraint against the actual `String` element, requiring constraint storage on the cast value or a wrapper that knows its declared inner type; (3) the class-aware ObjectValue refactor (PKL-148m parent dep тАФ `pipeOperator` res11 needs `new Person {}` to render with its class identity so the diagnostic projects `pipeOperator#Person` instead of bare `Object`)."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-148n" }
  tags { "evaluator"; "operator"; "upstream"; "compat" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

local silentMismatchSurvey: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-153"
  name = "Silent-mismatch survey"
  description =
    "The 148 upstream fixtures that evaluate without diagnostic but don't byte-match the gold output are the long tail тАФ typically rendering subtleties (whitespace, member ordering, string-escape choices, Listing element separator), output-block extraction edge cases, or trivial Float-format / number-stringification differences. Each one usually reads as a one-or-two-line PCF-renderer fix. The slice's deliverable is a tabulated categorization (by diff signature, captured into a checked-in CSV under `scripts/`) plus the highest-uplift bucket fixed end-to-end. Subsequent buckets land as their own micro-slices."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-096" }
  tags { "renderer"; "upstream"; "compat" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "minor"
}

entries: Listing<Spec.Scenario> = new {
  pklSuperLateBindAndAmendLambda
  upstreamResourceType
  asAndPipeRuntime
  silentMismatchSurvey
}

// тФАтФА DEFERRED тФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФА
// Slices intentionally parked on 2026-05-16. Spec.pkl does not import
// `deferredEntries`, so these stay out of the rendered SPEC.md and out
// of `pkspec spec --check`'s view; lifting any of them back into
// `entries` is a one-line move when a concrete consumer surfaces.

local pklRepl: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-101"
  name = "pkl repl interactive evaluator"
  description =
    "`moon run cmd/mpkl -- repl` opens an interactive read-eval-print loop: each line parses as either a binding (`x = 5`) or an expression and prints the rendered result. Reuses the `AnalysisSession` so each entry incrementally extends the module."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-009" }
  tags { "cli"; "repl"; "deferred" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "minor"
}

local xmlRenderer: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-126b"
  name = "xml renderer"
  description =
    "Emit Pkl objects as an XML element tree. Each property becomes an `<element-name>` node; listings render as repeated elements; mapping entries render with the key as the element name. The `xml.Element` and `xml.Inline` annotation classes from `pkl:xml` already exist (PKL-124); this slice wires the rendering side. `-f xml` and `output { renderer = new xml.Renderer { ... } }` both route here. Deferred because `pkl eval -f xml` upstream covers the same surface for consumers that need XML output today."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-124"; "PKL-126a" }
  tags { "renderer"; "xml"; "deferred" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

local protobufRenderer: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-126c"
  name = "protobuf renderer"
  description =
    "Serialize Pkl values against an externally provided `.proto` schema and emit the binary wire format. Requires a schema-lookup mechanism (the `pkl:protobuf` `Renderer` class carries the schema reference) and a way to surface bytes through the existing `BytesValue` carrier. Deferred for the same reason as PKL-126b тАФ Apple Pkl already covers the surface, and the `.proto` schema parser is a non-trivial separate lift."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-124"; "PKL-126a"; "PKL-126b" }
  tags { "renderer"; "protobuf"; "deferred" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

local rendererConverters: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-127"
  name = "renderer converter machinery"
  description =
    "JSON / YAML / Properties renderers honor `converters { [\"path\"] = (value) -> ...; [\"Class\"] = (value) -> ... }`. Path lookups beat class lookups; the converter return value replaces the source value in the rendered output. Deferred alongside the rest of the renderer surface; consumers needing the converter shape today route through `pkl eval` upstream."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-104" }
  tags { "renderer"; "converter"; "deferred" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

local pkldoc: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-130"
  name = "pkldoc documentation generation"
  description =
    "`moon run cmd/mpkl -- doc <module>` renders the module's class / typealias / function declarations as Markdown / HTML, using the doc-comment text already captured by the parser. Deferred because Apple Pkl's own `pkldoc` covers this surface; revisit if pkl-mbt-only authoring becomes a regular workflow."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-080" }
  tags { "cli"; "pkldoc"; "deferred" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "minor"
}

local lspServer: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-132"
  name = "LSP server foundation"
  description =
    "A Language Server Protocol server (stdio or socket transport) that surfaces hover, go-to-definition, find-references, completion, diagnostics, semantic tokens, and rename. The existing CST + typechecker + ripple-backed AnalysisSession provide the analysis substrate. Deferred тАФ editor tooling is downstream of the library scope and Apple's `pkl-lsp` already exists. Revisit if a MoonBit-native editor integration becomes a target."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-107" }
  tags { "lsp"; "editor"; "deferred" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

local packagePklRegistryUnpack: Spec.Scenario = new {
  id = "PKL-129b2"
  name = "package:// zipball download and unpack"
  description =
    "PKL-129b1 already lands the URI parse, metadata fetch, and `packageZipUrl` extraction with an actionable diagnostic. PKL-129b2 would close the loop: download the zipball over HTTPS, verify the SHA-256 checksum from `packageZipChecksums`, DEFLATE-decode the archive, cache the extracted tree under `~/.pkl/cache/package-2/<authority>/<path>/<version>/`, then resolve the fragment path against the cache. Deferred because the DEFLATE decoder isn't accessible standalone (mizchi/x and moonbitlang/async only expose it under gzip framing) and the ZIP central-directory parser is a several-hundred-line slice on top тАФ a multi-KLOC lift for thin marginal value over the PKL-129b1 diagnostic, which already tells users to run `pkl download-package` + `--module-path`. Revisit when a concrete library consumer needs end-to-end registry resolution without an Apple Pkl CLI dependency."
  contributes { "GOAL-PKL-PURE" }
  dependsOn { "PKL-129b1" }
  tags { "parser"; "imports"; "sandbox"; "pkf-pkspec"; "deferred" }
  reviewStatus = "draft"
  severity = "major"
}

deferredEntries: Listing<Spec.Scenario> = new {
  pklRepl
  xmlRenderer
  protobufRenderer
  rendererConverters
  pkldoc
